Cleveland





Cleveland, Ohio is more than just our headquarters—it's our hometown. 




Look forward to coming to work
The headquarters consists of two main campuses in the suburb of Mayfield Village, along with several smaller offices in the area. Employees enjoy cafeterias, healthcare facilities, fitness centers with classes, onsite restaurants and convenience stores and quiet rooms to relax and refresh. 
Embrace diversity, thrive on support
The offices are also home to all our employee resource groups: The Progressive African-American Network; Progressive's Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual and Transgender Network; the Progressive Latin American Networking Association; Progressive's Asian-American Network; and the Network of Empowered Women. These groups help foster a diverse and supportive work environment for all.
Our headquarters is the home of Progressive's Art Collection—the campuses and surrounding offices boast a wide variety of artwork. The art helps foster a spirit of creativity and innovation in the workplace.
Experience this plum of a city
Clevelanders embrace all the area has to offer. It's a dash of peaceful Midwest living with plenty of culture and excitement. 
The city boasts a theater district, a Museum of Art, the Rock n' Roll Hall of Fame, a world-renowned Orchestra and nightlife on East 4th Street.
The area has a couple of recreational gems. Lake Erie is the city's backyard, and offers watersports, fishing and miles of beaches. The Cleveland Metroparks is a network of 16 recreational areas—some just minutes from our campuses—with walking, biking and riding trails.




Play video



"CLE" is a digital short film about the greater Cleveland area told through a unique perspective of the people that live here and the city itself. Progressive would like to thank everyone who contributed to and inspired this film about our great city and its many surrounding areas.


